{"parse":{"title":"Certificate of public convenience and necessity","pageid":44853854,"revid":798005085,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>A <b>certificate of public convenience and necessity</b> or <b>certificate of public convenience</b> is a type of <a href=\"/wiki/Regulatory_compliance\" title=\"Regulatory compliance\">regulatory compliance</a> certification for <a href=\"/wiki/Public_service\" title=\"Public service\">public service</a> industries. <a href=\"/wiki/Private_companies\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Private companies\">Private companies</a> wishing to provide essential public services in certain countries must be granted a CPCN before constructing facilities and offering services.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Philippines\">Philippines</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Certificate_of_public_convenience_and_necessity&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Philippines\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In the Philippines, a certificate of public convenience (CPC) is required for private provision of public services for which no franchise, either municipal or legislative, is required by law, such as a <a href=\"/wiki/Common_carrier\" title=\"Common carrier\">common carrier</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"United_States\">United States</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Certificate_of_public_convenience_and_necessity&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: United States\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The first <a href=\"/wiki/U.S._state\" title=\"U.S. state\">U.S. state</a> statutes for certificate of public convenience (CPCN) were issued in 1870, and the <a href=\"/wiki/U.S._Congress\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"U.S. Congress\">U.S. Congress</a> included a certification provision in <a href=\"/wiki/U.S._federal_law\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"U.S. federal law\">U.S. federal law</a> in the <a href=\"/wiki/Transportation_Act_of_1920\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Transportation Act of 1920\">Transportation Act of 1920</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Examples of industries requiring a CPCN from a U.S. state include the provision of <a href=\"/wiki/Telecommunications\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Telecommunications\">telecommunications</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/New_York_(state)\" title=\"New York (state)\">New York</a> state,<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> transportation of <a href=\"/wiki/Natural_gas\" title=\"Natural gas\">natural gas</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Alaska\" title=\"Alaska\">Alaska</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> and a range of public services in <a href=\"/wiki/Illinois\" title=\"Illinois\">Illinois</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Certificate_of_public_convenience_and_necessity&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.batasnatin.com/law-library/mercantile-law/transportation-laws/2218-certificate-of-public-convenience-cpc.html\">\"What is a Certificate of Public Convenience (CPC)?\"</a>. <i>Philippine Law Library</i>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Philippine+Law+Library&amp;rft.atitle=What+is+a+Certificate+of+Public+Convenience+%28CPC%29%3F&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.batasnatin.com%2Flaw-library%2Fmercantile-law%2Ftransportation-laws%2F2218-certificate-of-public-convenience-cpc.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACertificate+of+public+convenience+and+necessity\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Jones, William K. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.jstor.org/discover/1121802?sid=21105515254613&amp;uid=2&amp;uid=4\">\"Origins of the Certificate of Public Convenience and Necessity: Developments in the States, 1870 - 1920\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Columbia_Law_Review\" title=\"Columbia Law Review\">Columbia Law Review</a></i>. <b>79</b> (3): 426\u2013516. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.2307/1121802\">10.2307/1121802</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Columbia+Law+Review&amp;rft.atitle=Origins+of+the+Certificate+of+Public+Convenience+and+Necessity%3A+Developments+in+the+States%2C+1870+-+1920&amp;rft.volume=79&amp;rft.issue=3&amp;rft.pages=426-516&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.2307%2F1121802&amp;rft.aulast=Jones&amp;rft.aufirst=William+K.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fdiscover%2F1121802%3Fsid%3D21105515254613%26uid%3D2%26uid%3D4&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACertificate+of+public+convenience+and+necessity\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www3.dps.ny.gov/W/PSCWeb.nsf/All/C78F4BE884AA2FA885257687006F3964?OpenDocument\">\"CPCN: Certificate of Public Convenience and Necessity\"</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/New_York_State_Public_Service_Commission\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New York State Public Service Commission\">New York State Public Service Commission</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">27 December</span> 2014</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=CPCN%3A+Certificate+of+Public+Convenience+and+Necessity&amp;rft.pub=New+York+State+Public+Service+Commission&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww3.dps.ny.gov%2FW%2FPSCWeb.nsf%2FAll%2FC78F4BE884AA2FA885257687006F3964%3FOpenDocument&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACertificate+of+public+convenience+and+necessity\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/15/720a\">\"15 U.S. Code \u00a7 720a - Issuance of certificate of public convenience and necessity\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Legal_Information_Institute\" title=\"Legal Information Institute\">Legal Information Institute</a></i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">27 December</span> 2014</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&a